look.title: Top Offsite Links

look.title: Top Downloaded Clicks
look.description: A table of Download File, Download count, and percent of total downloads, ordered by Download Count.

dashboard_elements.note_text: A Download click shows the count that users have clicked to download an asset linked to on your page.
dashboard_elements.note_text_as_html: A Download click shows the count that users have clicked to download an asset linked to on your page.

look.title: Time of Day and Day of Week Heatmap
look.description: A table showing the Day of Week as columns and Hour of Day rows counting sessions for each over the time frame specified by a Session Start Date range filter.

dashboard_elements.note_text: A table showing the day of week as columns and hour of day rows, counting sessions for each over the time frame specified by the date range in the filter section.
dashboard_elements.note_text_as_html: A table showing the day of week as columns and hour of day rows, counting sessions for each over the time frame specified by the date range in the filter section.

look.title: Unique Visits this Period and Percent Change Since Last Period
look.description: A key performance indicator showing the count of unique visits tracked in this period, with the percent difference as compared to the previous period. Requires a date range filter to return non-null values.

dashboard_elements.note_text: The record of a users presence and actions performed on a website. This may include multiple page views, events, etc. Previously in WebTrends, this was referred to as a Visit.
dashboard_elements.note_text_as_html: The record of a users presence and actions performed on a website. This may include multiple page views, events, etc. Previously in WebTrends, this was referred to as a Visit.

look.title: Page Views this Period and Percent Change Since Last Period - page views
look.description:
A key performance indicator showing the count of unique visits tracked in this period, with the percent difference as compared to the previous period. Requires a date range filter to return non-null values.

Note: This is the page views version. For the sessions version, see https://analytics.gov.bc.ca/looks/283

dashboard_elements.note_text: The number of times a web page has been viewed. A user can have multiple page views during a session. A high number of page views within a session may indicate users have navigated back to the page. It may be intentional, if page A is a hub for the rest of your content.
dashboard_elements.note_text_as_html: The number of times a web page has been viewed. A user can have multiple page views during a session. A high number of page views within a session may indicate users have navigated back to the page. It may be intentional, if page A is a hub for the rest of your content.

look.title: Average Session Duration this Period and Percent Change Since Last Period
look.description:
A key performance indicator showing the average session duration (as hh:mm:ss) tracked in this period, with the percent difference as compared to the previous period.

Requires a date range filter to return non-null values.

dashboard_elements.note_text: The average session duration calculates the average amount of time people stay on gov.bc.ca when they visit your pages. The percentage shows by how much the length of user sessions has increased or decreased over the selected date range.
dashboard_elements.note_text_as_html: The average session duration calculates the average amount of time people stay on gov.bc.ca when they visit your pages. The percentage shows by how much the length of user sessions has increased or decreased over the selected date range.

dashboard_elements.note_text:
"Top referral URLs" shows the most common URLs that are directing users to your site. It is ordered by page views count and shows the percentage of page views from this referral URL.

If you see a result containing this "statics.teams.cdn.office.net", the referrer is coming from a Microsoft Teams environment. For example, you shared the website link in a Teams chat, and folks are clicking on that link.

look.title: Traffic Map
look.description:
a map, centred on B.C., visualizing sessions by their geo-coordinates.

Note: This version of the map is based on the page views table. For the sessions version see: https://analytics.gov.bc.ca/looks/287

dashboard_elements.note_text: A map, centred on B.C., showing sessions by their geo locations (longitude and latitude). Dot size is based on session counts.
dashboard_elements.note_text_as_html: A map, centred on B.C., showing sessions by their geo locations (longitude and latitude). Dot size is based on session counts.

dashboard_elements.note_text: This tells you the search terms that people are using in Google Search, that are directing users to your site.

look.title: Page Views per Session this Period and Percent Change Since Last Period
look.description: A key performance indicator showing the number of Page Views per Session in this period, with the percent difference as compared to the previous period. Requires a date range filter to return non-null values.

dashboard_elements.note_text: The average number of pages that a user has viewed per session.
dashboard_elements.note_text_as_html: The average number of pages that a user has viewed per session.

look.title: Traffic Summary
look.description:
A bar graph of user counts, session counts, and page view counts; clustered by granularity defined with the Traffic Summary filter. Requires a date range filter and a Time Period to retrieve results, and a Traffic Summary filter to format the granularity on the x-axis.

Note: This version is for page views. For sessions see: https://analytics.gov.bc.ca/looks/282

dashboard_elements.note_text: This report summarizes page views, sessions, and users over the date range. Use the "Time Period" filter to determine whether this report is summarized by day, month, or year. When summarizing by month or year, it will include all dates in any month or year that overlaps the date range.
